				\begin{document}$\sim55~\text{km}$\end{document} at an altitude of 265 km. With the orbiter pointed to nadir, MMS can perform multi-sample hyperspectral mode imaging at full spectral resolution (0.379–1.076 μm with 2.73 nm/band, 1.033–3.425 μm with 7.5 nm/band, 2.1 km/pixel at 265 km). The multispectral mapping mode provides an additional observing option, a subset of 72 bands and binned to minimum pixel footprints of 265 m/pixel resolution. The nadir observation of MMS is described in Fig. 4. Fig. 4
Schematic representation of MMS’s nadir observation. The cryocooler needs to complete the cool the MCT FPA before reaching an orbital altitude of 800 km, and MMS performs nadir observation for 26 minutes approximately

