Schematic diagram of pixel binning principle. The raw spectral images are binned cross-track firstly. Then pixel binning along-track is performed as shown. The spatial and spectral resolution differs according to the operation mode after pixel binning preprocessing

In the multi-sample hyperspectral mode, MMS’s detectors are exposed globally and push-broom the surface of Mars at a rate of 20 Hz. After completing the blind pixel compensation on chip, 26-sample hyperspectral data is generated by the 16×\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
