Theoretically, the ratio of the radiometric calibration coefficients between the long integration time (44.635 ms) and the short integration time (5.155 ms) should be around 8.6 for all V-NIR bands. Even if the ratio is not around 8.6, it fluctuates at least around a constant. The ratios before smear removal vary significantly with bands, and the maximum value is more than 3 times the minimum value in 0.45–1.05 μm. Whereas the ratios after smear removal fluctuate within a range of 7.7±0.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
